  "prompt": "Has any Modi supporter turned into a Kejriwal supporter?",
  "response": "There have been reports and anecdotes of individuals who initially supported Prime Minister Narendra Modi and later shifted their support to Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal. Political allegiance can be fluid, and voters may change their preferences based on a variety of factors, such as performance, policy decisions, and personal experiences.\n\nThe dynamics of Indian politics are complex, especially in urban areas like Delhi, where issues such as governance, education, and health care can significantly impact public opinion. It's not uncommon for voters to reassess their choices based on how they perceive the effectiveness of the leaders in addressing local issues.\n\nHowever, specific statistics or comprehensive studies on the scale of such shifts might not be readily available. Political sentiment can vary widely across demographics and regions, leading to changes in support for different parties and leaders over time.",
